genresAdvancedInfo.name: chennai indie
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A subgenre of indie rock that emerged from the vibrant music scene in Chennai, India. Chennai indie is characterized by its eclectic mix of influences, including traditional Indian music, Western rock, and electronic music. The genre is known for its experimental soundscapes, socially conscious lyrics, and emphasis on improvisation and collaboration. Chennai indie artists often incorporate elements of Carnatic music, a classical South Indian music tradition, into their work, creating a unique and innovative sound.
